    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Cooling System, and
        Related Components - Removal - Secondary Compressor Support, Dual Idler Pulleys, and Idler Mounting Plate
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Secondary Compressor Support, Dual Idler Pulleys, and Idler Mounting Plate</title>
        <figure id="f3350012284" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK05/K05002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="368px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Dual Freon&#174; compressor mounting</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 110 bolt (8)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">A/C (Freon&#174;) compressor (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Secondary Freon&#174; compressor support</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 30 bolt (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 60 bolt (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Flat idler pulley assembly (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Idler mounting plate</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, do not open pressurized Freon&#174; lines.</para>
            </warning>
            <note>
                <para>The following procedure only applies to engines equipped with dual A/C (Freon&#174;)
                    compressors.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove four M8 x 110 bolts holding the outer Freon&#174; compressor to the secondary Freon&#174;
                compressor support.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Do not remove or disconnect pressurized Freon&#174; lines. Move outer Freon&#174; compressor
                out of the way and secure with a strap or remove from engine.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If required, remove two M10 x 60 bolts and remove two flat idler pulley assemblies.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If required, remove two M10 x 30 bolts and remove the idler mounting plate from the
                secondary Freon&#174; compressor support.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove four M8 x 110 bolts holding the secondary Freon&#174; compressor support and inner
                Freon&#174; compressor to the cylinder head.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
